Description: Fragment of marble bearing remains of incised Greek text filled with blue. Right edge but no rear surface preserved.
Curator's comments: The fragment is illustrated on one of Petrie's photographs, Delta series no. 367, which was captioned by Petrie (Petrie notebook 23) "Fragment of 2nd temple of Apollo", thus suggesting that the piece was found in the sanctuary of Apollo.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (BA.06)
